  <div class="prose about-prose">
    <p>
        I'm a software engineer who works across different levels of a
system, from embedded systems to mobile applications and backend
services. I like to understand the business goals behind a project
and make technical decisions that support those goals.
    </p>
    <p>
        Throughout
my career, I have worked across these different layers: from building
embedded products and their companion applications to developing
an iOS SDK for the automotive industry. Not only do I work on
implementation, but I also contribute to architectural discussions
and decisions, document the software, and capture the reasoning
behind technical choices throughout a project's lifecycle.
    </p>
    <p>
        In my free time, I build
projects to explore technologies and ideas. Through NC-750, I
experiment with how privacy-oriented and user-controlled software
could be designed. Mirror, its first project, explores how modern AI
tools can be integrated into practical workflows while keeping users
in control of their data.
    </p>
    <p>
        Outside of technical work, my time goes to my homelab, music, video games, cinema, and discovering new things and cultures.
    </p>
